{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Jhn|10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","chapter":10,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":1,"text":"“Truly I tell you, anyone who doesn’t enter the sheep pen by the gate but climbs in some other way is a thief and a robber.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":2,"text":"The one who enters by the gate is the shepherd of the sheep.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":3,"text":"The gatekeeper opens it for him, and the sheep hear his voice. He calls his own sheep by name and leads them out.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":4,"text":"When he has brought all his own outside, he goes ahead of them. The sheep follow him because they know his voice.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":5,"text":"They will never follow a stranger; instead they will run away from him, because they don’t know the voice of strangers.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":6,"text":"Jesus gave them this figure of speech, but they did not understand what he was telling them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":7,"text":"Jesus said again, “Truly I tell you, I am the gate for the sheep.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":8,"text":"All who came before me are thieves and robbers, but the sheep didn’t listen to them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":9,"text":"I am the gate. If anyone enters by me, he will be saved and will come in and go out and find pasture.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":10,"text":"A thief comes only to steal and kill and destroy. I have come so that they may have life and have it in abundance.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":11,"text":"“I am the good shepherd. Ps 23 The good shepherd lays down his life for the sheep.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":12,"text":"The hired hand, since he is not the shepherd and doesn’t own the sheep, leaves them and runs away when he sees a wolf coming. The wolf then snatches and scatters them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":13,"text":"This happens because he is a hired hand and doesn’t care about the sheep.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":14,"text":"“I am the good shepherd. I know my own, and my own know me,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":15,"text":"just as the Father knows me, and I know the Father. I lay down my life for the sheep.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":16,"text":"But I have other sheep that are not from this sheep pen; I must bring them also, and they will listen to my voice. Then there will be one flock, one shepherd.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":17,"text":"This is why the Father loves me, because I lay down my life so that I may take it up again.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":18,"text":"No one takes it from me, but I lay it down on my own. I have the right to lay it down, and I have the right to take it up again. I have received this command from my Father.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":19,"text":"Again the Jews were divided because of these words.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":20,"text":"Many of them were saying, “He has a demon and he’s crazy. Why do you listen to him?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":21,"text":"Others were saying, “These aren’t the words of someone who is demon-possessed. Can a demon open the eyes of the blind?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":22,"text":"Then the Festival of Dedication took place in Jerusalem, and it was winter.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":23,"text":"Jesus was walking in the temple in Solomon’s Colonnade.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":24,"text":"The Jews surrounded him and asked, “How long are you going to keep us in suspense? If you are the Messiah, tell us plainly.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":25,"text":"“I did tell you and you don’t believe,” Jesus answered them. “The works that I do in my Father’s name testify about me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":26,"text":"But you don’t believe because you are not of my sheep.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":27,"text":"My sheep hear my voice, I know them, and they follow me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":28,"text":"I give them eternal life, and they will never perish. No one will snatch them out of my hand.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":29,"text":"My Father, who has given them to me, is greater than all. No one is able to snatch them out of the Father’s hand.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":30,"text":"I and the Father are one.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:31","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":31,"text":"Again the Jews picked up rocks to stone him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:32","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":32,"text":"Jesus replied, “I have shown you many good works from the Father. For which of these works are you stoning me?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:33","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":33,"text":"“We aren’t stoning you for a good work,” the Jews answered, “but for blasphemy, because you —being a man —make yourself God.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:34","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":34,"text":"Jesus answered them, “Isn’t it written in your law, I said, you are gods?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:35","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":35,"text":"If he called those to whom the word of God came ‘gods’ —and the Scripture cannot be broken —","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:36","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":36,"text":"do you say, ‘You are blaspheming’ to the one the Father set apart and sent into the world, because I said: I am the Son of God?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:37","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":37,"text":"If I am not doing my Father’s works, don’t believe me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:38","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":38,"text":"But if I am doing them and you don’t believe me, believe the works. This way you will know and understand that the Father is in me and I in the Father.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:39","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":39,"text":"Then they were trying again to seize him, but he escaped their grasp.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:40","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":40,"text":"So he departed again across the Jordan to the place where John had been baptizing earlier, and he remained there.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:41","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":41,"text":"Many came to him and said, “John never did a sign, but everything John said about this man was true.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jhn:10:42","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","bookOrder":42,"chapter":10,"verse":42,"text":"And many believed in him there.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jhn","chapter":10,"paragraphStarts":[1,7,11,14,19,22,25,31,32,33,34,40],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"The Good Shepherd"},{"beforeVerse":22,"text":"Jesus at the Festival of Dedication"},{"beforeVerse":31,"text":"Renewed Efforts to Stone Jesus"},{"beforeVerse":40,"text":"Many beyond the Jordan Believe in Jesus"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-0